text.inkscape:label: Story start
text.tspan: Your parents made you visit your creepy uncle this year. Despite all
your protests they forced you to go. You don't really know what it
is about him that creeps you out so much, maybe it was the way he
always seemed to undress you with his eyes.
Maybe it was something totally else, all you know is that he always
makes you feel uncomfortable.

text.tspan: Why did my parents make me do this?
As soon as you arrive a chill goes down your spine. The
mansion seems even creepier now as the snow falls down.
Through the clouds the only light comes from the full
moon in the sky.
You slowly walk up to the door and take a deep breath
before you ring the doorbell. It takes a few minutes
before the old butler opens the door.
